!Example: print("print('what to print')")	or print('print("what to print")')

\n			-- new line within a print statement 

print("Hello" + " " + "Angela")		-- concatenation of different strings

start to code in the beggining of the line

# 
print("Hello " + input("What is your name? "))		-- nested code input for print statement
first it will initiate input function, then it will futfill the print statement

Ctrl + l   			-- comment line
Ctrl + z			-- uncomment line 

print( len (input("") ) )		-- prints lenght of input that we type

