========================================
Data types

String			"Hello"[0] 		-- brackets shows the letter from the string starting from 0
#Data Types

#String
print("Hello"[4])			-- prints the string letter 5 (o)

#Integer
print(123 + 345)
print(123_456_789)

#Float
3.14159

#Boolean
True
False

PEMDASLR
Parentheses			-- ()
Exponents			-- **
Multipliation		-- * 
Division			-- / 
Addition			-- +
Subtraction			-- -

Rounding numbers
ex:
print(round(8/3, 2))		-- shows the rounding result to the second number after the decimal point
!!Advanced rounding:
final_amount = "{:.2f}".format(bill per person)		-- givs the output the format of number up to the second digit after decimal point


Floor division:
print(8 // 3)				-- will show only one number and it will be in integer type

Whenever we want to calculate the same value, we can use "+=" or -= and etc. to show up an updated value:
ex.:
score = 0
score += 1			-- adds 1 to the score value
print(score)		-- it will print 1

f-String			-- puts different types of data and makes them printable
ex.: 		score = 0
			height = 1.8
			isWinning = True
			print(f"your score is {score}, your height is {height}, you are winning is {isWinning}")
			
